OL,4,Cpupil behaviour, survey says
OL,6,F"Thirteen per cent of members said
OL,7,Fhalf their lessons were interrupted
OL,8,Fbut, more worryingly, 75% said the
OL,9,Fmajority to all their lessons were
OL,10,Finterrupted."
OL,12,FMembers also said pupils were caught
OL,13,Fusing their phones to play games,
OL,14,Flisten to music, watch TV shows, and
OL,15,Feven to contact their parents to
OL,16,Fcomplain about school staff.
OL,18,FSome 86% of respondents said they ask
OL,19,Fpupils to put their phones away, with
OL,20,F83% telling them to put their phones
OL,21,Fin school bags.
